When I try to delete all plans and projects to reset the Bamboo instance in my integration tests with 

{code:java}
for (Project project: projectManager.getAllProjects()) {
    for (Plan plan: project.getPlans()) {
        planManager.deletePlan(plan);
    }
    projectManager.deleteProject(project);
}

{code}

I always get the following exception:


{noformat}
[tSessionImpl] Could not synchronize database state with session
 
[INFO] [talledLocalContainer] org.springframework.jdbc.UncategorizedSQLException: 
Hibernate operation: Could not execute JDBC batch update; uncategorized SQLException for SQL []; SQL state [null]; error code [0]; failed batch; nested exception is java.sql.BatchUpdateException: failed batch
{noformat}

Any ideas what I do wrong? How can I reset a Bamboo instance during my tests otherwise?

The following fields are currently available on the *rest/api/latest/result* api
{noformat}
buildTestSummary  . . . . . : 2 of 872 failed
successfulTestCount . . . . : 765
failedTestCount . . . . . . : 2
quarantinedTestCount  . . . : 44
skippedTestCount  . . . . . : 61
{noformat}

This is good for reporting, but it is missing a critical piece of information. That is how many of the quarantined tests are now actually successful or conversely, how many are still failing. In my case, 5 are failing and the other 39 are now ok. I need something like:
{noformat}
failedQuarantinedTestCount: 5
{noformat}

Reporting accurately the status of all builds is really important when you have hundreds of builds and quarantining is used.
